<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="168" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[113,1089,219,819]" pageId="7" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,242,732,755]" pageId="7" pageNumber="168">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet (masculine) refers to the three colors observed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Anton &amp; Delobel" authorityYear="2017" box="[972,1081,732,755]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Bruchidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis box="[972,1081,732,755]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="168">B. tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: black and reddish-brown of the integument, and greyish of the dorsal vestiture.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
